Jesus is coming

He is God who came to live as man, who did not sin.

snippet.textDisplay:
Loved this . I sang these songs as a kid in the school choir we put on the show at a local theatre. I grew up enchained and isolated. At 51 have had a life long appreciation of this musical. So was wonderful to watch . I wouldn’t be able to buy right now though have bought this as a present many years ago.
I also have prophetic dreams like 9:11, Concorde, tsunami, the last bank crash and why it happened and the future result which I believe is playing out now. We have had the cycle of drought, fires, floods, locusts and now the “plague” - time to start a new cycle of helping each other be creative, freely generously and joyfully. Reducing some of the red tape and taxes on just being friendly, and swapping skills and services. Appreciating the Collective collaboration that keeps us all alive. And replacing and repairing that which we have taken from Mother Earth to help future planet-living. Much love 💕
